A car rental company wants to calculate the daily rental price for different types of cars.
They have several car categories:
• Sedan
• SUV
• Truck

Even though all of them are cars, each type has a different pricing rule.
You must use polymorphism so that each car type provides its own version of the calculatePrice() method.
Your tasks:
1. Create a Parent Class
Fields: brand, year, name
Method: calculatePrice() (returns a base price, e.g., 0 or default)

2. Create Child Classes
Sedan = First day 50, next day 30 per day
SUV = First day 80, next day 75 per day
Truck = First day 120, next day 115 per day

3. Create a Program to
• Insert Car
• Rent Car
• Return Car
• Remove Car

Insert Car
• Ask user to input car name, brand, and year
• Add car to the array list

Rent Car
• Show all available cars
• Ask user to choose car (by index) and input day
• Calculate price

Return Car
• Show all rented cars
• Ask user to choose car
• Change the car status into available

Remove Car
• Ask user to choose car to be deleted
• Remove car from the Array List

